<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I agree</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Elistran">Elistran</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:00 p.m. 19/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I agree<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2062" TARGET=_self>Outstanding PvP Issues - are we in agreement?</A> (TheBlack)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I agree with most of what you said, in particular I think that /con should only tell you whether the person is within your range, and I like the idea of green if they are too low, red if they are too high and white/blue in-between. I also think that you should be able to attack anyone of a higher level than you (in many cases it would be suicide, but sometimes your friend gets attacked by someone who is only 5-6 levels higher than you and you cannot help, even though your aid might sway the battle).

<P>As for increasing the level limits as you go up in level, this really depends on the relative strength of the different classes as their level increases. As it stands now, you at least have a chance to flee in many cases if you get jumped by someone higher than you are. If the level range is increased to 8 at level 50, perhaps the power difference would be so overwhelming that there would be no chance for a level 42-43 to get away. Having never had a character that high level, I don't know how the relative strengths work out, perhaps someone with more experience might have some input? If the difference between a level 42 and a level 50 is comparable to that between a level 17 and a level 13, this would be a nice addition. If on the other hand, the power difference between a level 50 and a level 42 is the same as that between a level 8 and a level 1, I don’t think I would support increasing the level range.
<P>Elistran L'Toth
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
